.TH "dmam_pool_create" 9 "dmam_pool_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dmam_pool_create \- Managed dma_pool_create()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct dma_pool *" dmam_pool_create
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "size_t align "  ","
.BI "size_t allocation "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
name of pool, for diagnostics
.IP "dev" 12
device that will be doing the DMA
.IP "size" 12
size of the blocks in this pool.
.IP "align" 12
alignment requirement for blocks; must be a power of two
.IP "allocation" 12
returned blocks won't cross this boundary (or zero)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed \fBdma_pool_create\fP.  DMA pool created with this function is
automatically destroyed on driver detach.
.SH "RETURN"
a managed dma allocation pool with the requested
characteristics, or NULL if one can't be created.
